Here&#39;s what solved my issue. At the end I think I focused too much on using fetch.
I realized that I could use the API query url to initiate the download using the download attribute compatible with Google Chrome.

```
    var link = document.createElement(&quot;a&quot;);
    link.download = name;
    link.href = uri;
    document.body.appendChild(link);
    link.click();
    document.body.removeChild(link);
    delete link;
```

Much more simple and no caching.

